-- Suspicious Package on Board Cargo Plane Not Sent to Berlusconi, Sky Says
-- B y   A n d r e w   D a v i s
-- 2010-11-02T23:39:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/suspicious-package-on-board-cargo-plane-not-sent-to-berlusconi-sky-says.html
A suspicious package found on board a
cargo plane bound from Athens to Paris that made an emergency
landing in Bologna, Italy was not addressed to Prime Minister
Silvio Berlusconi, Sky Italy reported, citing officials at the
airport.  The pilot requested an emergency landing after the package
was discovered and touched down about 10:15 p.m. local time, Sky
reported. The airport remains closed, the television network
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Davis at 
 abdavis@bloomberg.net  